'''获取COVID-19工具加速器'''（Access to COVID-19 Tools Accelerator）又稱'''ACT加速计划'''，是一个跨学科的支持平台，目的是使平台上的合作伙伴能够共享资源和分享知识以對抗[[2019冠狀病毒病疫情|2019冠狀病毒病疫情]]。它分為四个支柱，每个支柱由两到三个合作伙伴管理。<ref name="act-faq">{{Cite web|title=The ACT-Accelerator: frequently asked questions (FAQ)|url=https://www.who.int/initiatives/act-accelerator/faq|accessdate=16 December 2020|date=2020|publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]] (WHO)|archive-date=2021-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210504125946/https://www.who.int/initiatives/act-accelerator/faq|dead-url=no}}</ref>

* 疫苗（又称[[COVAX|COVAX]]，致力于全球公平获取[[2019冠状病毒病疫苗|2019冠状病毒病疫苗]]）
* 诊断
* 治疗
* 卫生系统

获取COVID-19工具加速器始於[[二十國集團|二十國集團]]于2020年4月24日宣布的一项倡议。[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]很快于4月24日響應<ref name="g20gm">{{Cite news|title=G20 launches initiative for health tools needed to combat the coronavirus|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-g20-launches-initiative-for-health-tools-needed-to-combat-the-2/|date=25 April 2020|ref=The Globe and Mail Inc|accessdate=2021-02-03|archive-date=2020-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200427134921/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-g20-launches-initiative-for-health-tools-needed-to-combat-the-2/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="whopress">{{Cite news|title=Access to COVID-19 Tools (ACT) Accelerator|url=https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/access-to-covid-19-tools-(act)-accelerator-call-to-action-24april2020.pdf|publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]] (WHO)|date=24 April 2020|accessdate=2021-02-03|archive-date=2020-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200425194644/https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/access-to-covid-19-tools-(act)-accelerator-call-to-action-24april2020.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2020年9月10日，[[联合国|联合国]]和[[欧洲联盟|欧洲联盟]]共同主办了'''获取COVID-19工具加速计划促进委员会'''成立会议，该委员会當時就收到了計劃籌款中的350亿美元中的27亿美元，以确保平台能提供20亿剂[[2019冠狀病毒病疫苗|2019冠狀病毒病疫苗]]、2.45亿个疗程和5亿次检测目标<ref>{{Cite web|title=Leaders pledge ‘quantum leap’ towards fully funding COVID-19 vaccines and treatments|url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2020/09/1072072|accessdate=2020-09-11|date=2020-09-10|work=UN News|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914162950/https://news.un.org/en/story/2020/09/1072072|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

截至2020年12月，發達國家已预购100多亿剂仍在研发中的候选COVID-19疫苗<ref name="mullard">{{Cite journal|title=How COVID vaccines are being divvied up around the world Canada leads the pack in terms of doses secured per capita|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-03370-6|last=Asher Mullard|date=30 November 2020|journal=Nature|accessdate=11 December 2020|doi=10.1038/d41586-020-03370-6|pmid=33257891|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122062947/https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-03370-6|dead-url=no}}</ref>。由于發達国家2021年的疫苗需求量很大<ref>{{Cite web|title=COVAX: Ensuring global equitable access to COVID-19 vaccines|url=https://www.gavi.org/covid19/covax-facility|publisher=Gavi|access-date=2021-02-03|archive-date=2020-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925122717/https://www.gavi.org/covid19/covax-facility/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="So">{{Cite journal|title=Reserving coronavirus disease 2019 vaccines for global access: cross sectional analysis|last=So|first=Anthony D|last2=Woo|first2=Joshua|date=2020-12-15|journal=BMJ|doi=10.1136/bmj.m4750|page=m4750|issn=1756-1833|subscription=free}}</ref>，低收入的发展中国家的人们可能要到2023年或2024年才能从[[2019冠状病毒病疫苗|2019冠状病毒病疫苗]]制造商那裡获得疫苗，COVAX就能在此時發揮作用<ref name="apuzzo">{{Cite news|author=Matt Apuzzo|author2=Selam Gebrekidan|title=For Covid-19 Vaccines, Some Are Too Rich — and Too Poor|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/28/world/africa/covid-19-vaccines-south-africa.html|accessdate=29 December 2020|work=The New York Times|date=28 December 2020|archive-date=2021-05-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210509085837/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/28/world/africa/covid-19-vaccines-south-africa.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
